  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The predicted patches are then unpatched into 3D keypoint trajectories, expressed in the camera coordinate frame.",
    "These trajectories can be executed using various low-level controllers; in our experiments, we apply inverse kinematics to map predicted 3D traces to robot joint commands. 4.",
    "1.1Multi-Encoder Feature Extraction RGB encoders.",
    "We adopt a multi-stream encoding strategy that captures complementary visual representations.",
    "For each RGB input image I ∈ R H×W ×3, we extract features using two frozen pretrained encoders:• DINOv3 [40]: A self-supervised vision transformer (ViT-L/16) that produces spatially-aware geometric featuresF dino ∈ R N ×D d. • SigLIP[56]: A vision-language model (SigLIP-Base-Patch16-384) that generates semantically aligned features F siglip ∈ R N ×Ds suitable for text-conditioned prediction."
  ],
